y 3. · (Optional) Bend your knees and let your feet rest on a bench or a box or something (90 degree angle on knees) 4. · Lift your head and torso **while bending your back forward** (if you don''t it''s a sit-up and also involves some back muscles). · The higher you go, the more you should feel your abs contracting. · 5.", "regression": "Go back to starting position an repeat", "safety": "[''Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground.'', ''Hold a weight plate or dumbbell on your chest.'', ''Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your shoulder blades are off the ground.'', ''Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position.'', ''Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.'']"}'::jsonb,
